cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for phenotype prediction based on genotype and environment data. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, specifically in the sub-field of deep learning (cs.LG). The use of deep neural networks also involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for image analysis and feature extraction. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization process and the use of residual learning, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and data structures (cs.DS).
